Statistics of DPR Korea League in the 2011 season.
==Overview== The championship was played over six rounds, after which the top four teams – [[April 25 Sports Club|April 25]], [[Kigwancha Sports Club|Kigwanch'a]], [[Sobaeksu Sports Club|Sobaeksu]], and [[Amrokkang Sports Club|Amrokkang]] – played a final tournament in [[Pyongyang|P'yŏngyang]] in November 2011, which was won by April 25.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesn/nkor2011.html|title=North Korea 2011|author=|date=|website=www.rsssf.com|accessdate=15 November 2018}}</ref>
