{{use dmy dates|date=April 2015}} {{infobox country at games | NOC = CRC | NOCname = Comité Olímpico de Costa Rica | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1976 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.concrc.org }}&nbsp;{{es icon}} | location = [[Montreal]] | competitors = 5 (4 men, 1 woman) | sports = 4 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Costa Rica]]''' competed at the '''[[1976 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada. Five competitors, four men and one woman, took part in nine events in four sports.<ref name="sports-reference">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/CRC/summer/1976/ |title=Costa Rica at the 1976 Montreal Summer Games |accessdate=18 April 2015 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>
==Archery== {{main|Archery at the 1976 Summer Olympics}} In its first archery competition at the Olympics, Costa Rica entered two men. They included the last place finisher.
'''Men's Individual Competition''': * [[Juan Wedel]] &mdash; 2165 points (→ 34th place) * [[Luis Gonzalez (archer)|Luis Gonzalez]] &mdash; 2005 points (→ 37th place)
==Cycling== {{main|Cycling at the 1976 Summer Olympics}} One cyclist represented Costa Rica in 1976.
;[[Cycling at the 1976 Summer Olympics – Men's individual road race|Individual road race]] * [[Carlos Alvarado Reyes|Carlos Alvarado]] &mdash; did not finish (→ no ranking)
