{{Infobox stadium | name = Estadio Eladio Rosabal Cordero | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Estadio Rosabal Cordero.jpg | caption = The stadium seen from the southwestern stand | fullname = Eladio Rosabal Cordero | former_names = | location = [[Heredia, Costa Rica|Heredia]], [[Costa Rica]] | coordinates = {{Coord|9.99963|-84.123065|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1951 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = artificial | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 7,700<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.herediano.com/nuestro-estadio |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-12-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210125449/http://herediano.com/nuestro-estadio |archivedate=2015-02-10 |df= }}</ref> | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[C.S. Herediano|Herediano]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''Estadio Eladio Rosabal Cordero''' is a multi-purpose [[stadium]] in [[Heredia, Costa Rica|Heredia]], [[Costa Rica]]. The stadium holds 7,700 people and opened in 1951. It is currently used mostly for [[association football|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[C.S. Herediano|Herediano]].
The stadium is named after Herediano legend [[Eladio Rosabal Cordero]], who founded the club in 1921.
