{{Infobox football biography | name = Ismet Sinani | fullname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1999|5|31|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Belluno]], Italy<ref>{{cite web|publisher=TuttoCalciatori|url=https://www.tuttocalciatori.net/Sinani_Ismet|title=Profile by TuttoCalciatori|language=Italian|accessdate=22 October 2018}}</ref> | image = | height = | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = [[S.S. Juve Stabia|Juve Stabia]] | clubnumber = 17 | youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2018 | youthclubs1 = [[A.C. Milan Youth Sector|Milan]] | years1 = 2018– | clubs1 = [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] | caps1 = 0 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2018– | clubs2 = → [[S.S. Juve Stabia|Juve Stabia]] (loan) | caps2 = 2 | goals2 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2015 | nationalteam1 = [[Albania national under-17 football team|Albania U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 5 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2017 | nationalteam2 = [[Albania national under-19 football team|Albania U19]] | nationalcaps2 = 3 | nationalgoals2 = 1 | nationalyears3 = 2018– | nationalteam3 = [[Kosovo national under-19 football team|Kosovo U19]] | nationalcaps3 = 3 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | pcupdate = 20 October 2018 | ntupdate = 27 March 2018 }} '''Ismet Sinani''' (born 31 May 1999) is an [[Italy|Italian]]-born [[Kosovo|Kosovan]] [[association football|football]] player. He plays in Italy for [[S.S. Juve Stabia|Juve Stabia]] on loan from [[A.C. Milan|Milan]]. He also represented Albania internationally before switching his allegiance to Kosovo.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[A.C. Milan|Milan]]|url=https://www.acmilan.com/it/news/show/br_76417|title=ALBANIA UNDER 17: MILAN, CONVOCATO ISMET SINANI|trans-title=Ismet Sinani called up to Albania Under 17|date=6 April 2015|language=Italian}}</ref>
==Club career== ===Milan=== He is a product of [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] academy and played for their [[A.C. Milan Youth Sector|Under-19 squad]] beginning in the 2015–16 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[A.C. Milan|Milan]]|url=https://www.acmilan.com/it/news/show/159114|title=GIOVANI ROSSONERI: BENE GLI ALLIEVI|trans-title=Youth Red-Blacks: Good Students|date=21 October 2015|language=Italian}}</ref>
====Loan to Juve Stabia==== Sinani joined third-tier [[Serie C]] club [[S.S. Juve Stabia|Juve Stabia]] on loan for the 2018–19 season on 31 August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[S.S. Juve Stabia|Juve Stabia]]|url=http://ssjuvestabia.it/blog/presi-cotticelli-sinani-ceduto-chirullo/|title=Presi Cotticelli e Sinani, ceduto Chirullo|trans-title=Cotticelli and Sinani join, Chirullo leaves|language=Italian|date=31 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[A.C. Milan|Milan]]|url=https://www.acmilan.com/it/news/media/2018-09-04/comunicato-ufficiale-le-cessioni-dal-settore-giovanile|title=COMUNICATO UFFICIALE: LE CESSIONI DAL SETTORE GIOVANILE|trans-title=Official Communication: Departures from the Youth Sector|date=4 September 2018|language=Italian}}</ref> He made his [[Serie C]] debut for Juve Stabia on 30 September 2018 in a game against [[Paganese Calcio 1926|Paganese]] as a 77th-minute substitute for [[Salvatore Elia]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/09/30/italy/serie-c1/paganese-calcio-1926/ss-juve-stabia/2919678/|title=Game Report by Soccerway|date=30 September 2018}}</ref>
