{{Use Pakistani English|date=September 2012}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}} {{Infobox venue | stadium_name = Sialkot Hockey Stadium | capicity = 48000 | image = | location = [[Sialkot]], [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 2004 | opened = 2008 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Sialkot District Government]] | operator = [[Pakistan Hockey Federation]] | surface = [[AstroTurf]] | Constructor = | construction_cost = PKR 1002 Million | area = {{convert|25|acre|m2}} | architect = | former_names = | nicknames = Sialkot Hockey Club | tenants = <center>Silkot District Hockey Team [[Crescent Hockey Club]]</center> | seating_capacity = 5,000 | dimensions = }}
'''Sialkot Hockey Stadium''' is a large [[Field Hockey]] [[stadium]] in [[Sialkot]], [[Pakistan]]. Its pitch is made of [[AstroTurf]]. Necessary arrangements are being finalized for development work on the Sialkot Hockey Stadium which will cost [[Pakistani rupee|Rs]] 1002 million. A pavilion, dressing rooms and stands for spectators will be constructed. It is located at Pasrur Road,<ref>{{cite web|title=Pasrur Road|url=http://ilovefakegrass.blogspot.co.uk/|website=The New Home of Pakistan Hockey}}</ref> Sialkot near Gulsahan-i-Iqbal Park. 1st international match will be played between Indian Junior Hockey Team and Pakistan Junior Hockey Team on 18 November 2008.
