The '''Togo national rugby union team''' represents [[Togo]] in international [[rugby union]]. Togo are a member of the [[International Rugby Board]] (IRB), and have yet to play in a [[Rugby World Cup]] tournament. Togo played their first international in 2001, losing to [[Nigeria national rugby union team|Nigeria]]. They won their first match in 2003, defeating [[Mauritania national rugby union team|Mauritania]].

